1
00:00:01,584 --> 00:00:02,711
I'm sorry, okay?

2
00:00:02,794 --> 00:00:06,214
[Tersa] <i>I just remembered</i>
<i>my other son, Gabriel.</i>

3
00:00:06,297 --> 00:00:07,841
<i>He's my youngest.</i>

4
00:00:08,341 --> 00:00:11,052
<i>We lost him 30 years ago.</i>

5
00:00:11,636 --> 00:00:15,640
<i>Sorry, I know it's been a long time, but…</i>

6
00:00:15,724 --> 00:00:16,599
[breathes heavily]

7
00:00:16,683 --> 00:00:20,603
<i>…I can't stop feeling sad</i>
<i>whenever I remember my son.</i>

8
00:00:20,687 --> 00:00:22,021
[Teresa sobs]

9
00:00:22,105 --> 00:00:23,606
[Jalil] <i>Doc, I understand you.</i>

10
00:00:24,357 --> 00:00:26,025
I'm adopted.

11
00:00:26,109 --> 00:00:29,696
[Jalil] <i>I don't know anything</i>
<i>about my real family.</i>

12
00:00:29,779 --> 00:00:31,823
<i>But I think about them sometimes.</i>

13
00:00:31,906 --> 00:00:33,908
I wonder if they’re still looking for me.

14
00:00:33,992 --> 00:00:35,660
[Jalil] <i>I never felt</i>
<i>like I was missing something.</i>

15
00:00:35,744 --> 00:00:39,247
<i>I owe that to the family</i>
<i>who took care of me.</i>

16
00:00:39,330 --> 00:00:41,499
<i>I'm forever grateful to them, Doc.</i>

17
00:00:41,583 --> 00:00:45,086
<i>I’ll return all the love they’ve given me.</i>

18
00:00:45,795 --> 00:00:49,340
[Marcus] <i>Mark my words.</i>
<i>I'll solve this case.</i>

19
00:00:49,424 --> 00:00:52,343
<i>No one will ever</i>
<i>fall victim to them again.</i>

20
00:00:52,427 --> 00:00:53,678
[man] <i>We followed the Muslim.</i>

21
00:00:53,762 --> 00:00:54,804
<i>That Usman Sabdani.</i>

22
00:00:54,888 --> 00:00:57,348
You're right, ma'am.
He meets up with Marcus Reyes.

23
00:00:57,432 --> 00:00:59,476
[man] <i>They always</i>
<i>go to this abandoned place.</i>

24
00:00:59,559 --> 00:01:00,685
They seem to be hiding something.

25
00:01:00,769 --> 00:01:02,020
It must be Datu Rahman.

26
00:01:02,854 --> 00:01:04,022
[Rashid] <i>I saw Usman.</i>

27
00:01:04,105 --> 00:01:05,774
<i>He was acting suspiciously.</i>

28
00:01:05,857 --> 00:01:07,734
<i>What's even more bizarre is that</i>

29
00:01:07,817 --> 00:01:09,986
<i>I saw Marcus Reyes</i>
<i>coming out of the same house</i>

30
00:01:10,070 --> 00:01:10,987
<i>the other night.</i>

31
00:01:11,071 --> 00:01:13,406
People who go to places like that

32
00:01:13,490 --> 00:01:16,284
are definitely hiding something.

33
00:01:16,367 --> 00:01:17,285
[sinister music playing]

34
00:01:17,368 --> 00:01:18,703
[man grunts]

35
00:01:21,122 --> 00:01:21,831
[man 1] Check there!

36
00:01:22,415 --> 00:01:23,750
[man 2] Nothing here, Boss!

37
00:01:23,833 --> 00:01:26,753
[suspenseful music playing]

38
00:01:26,836 --> 00:01:31,841
[mysterious theme music playing]

39
00:01:42,101 --> 00:01:44,312
[suspenseful music playing]

40
00:01:47,106 --> 00:01:49,192
[suspenseful music continues]

41
00:01:56,074 --> 00:01:56,908
[man] Over here!

42
00:01:56,991 --> 00:01:59,035
[grunts, panting]

43
00:01:59,119 --> 00:02:01,246
[panting]

44
00:02:05,667 --> 00:02:06,584
Check there!

45
00:02:09,587 --> 00:02:10,588
[phone chimes]

46
00:02:15,301 --> 00:02:16,427
[man] Get him!

47
00:02:16,511 --> 00:02:18,930
[Datu Rahman] <i>What do you want from me?!</i>

48
00:02:19,013 --> 00:02:20,390
[music intensifies]

49
00:02:20,473 --> 00:02:22,016
[Usman] Someone's found Datu Rahman!

50
00:02:23,226 --> 00:02:24,227
This can't be!

51
00:02:24,310 --> 00:02:26,813
- Leave me alone, you animals! [grunts]
- [man] Shut up!

52
00:02:26,896 --> 00:02:28,314
- Stop talking!
- [Datu Rahman groans]

53
00:02:28,398 --> 00:02:29,566
- [man 1] Bring him out!
- [man 2] Go!

54
00:02:30,191 --> 00:02:31,776
[tires screech]

55
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:33,570
- [man] Come on! Move it!
- [Datu Rahman grunts]

56
00:02:33,653 --> 00:02:34,821
- [man] <i>Hurry!</i>
- [tires screeching]

57
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:38,158
[man] Move!

58
00:02:38,241 --> 00:02:42,036
[tense music continues]

59
00:02:42,704 --> 00:02:44,455
- [Datu Rahman groans]
- [man] Move it!

60
00:02:47,834 --> 00:02:49,168
[man 1] Get him in the car!

61
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:51,087
[man 2] Move!

62
00:02:53,464 --> 00:02:54,841
- [man 3] Get inside!
- [Datu Rahman grunts]

63
00:02:54,924 --> 00:02:57,385
- [tense music swells]
- [Datu Rahman grunts]

64
00:02:57,468 --> 00:03:01,014
[phone buzzing]

65
00:03:01,931 --> 00:03:03,016
Hello?

66
00:03:03,099 --> 00:03:04,642
[henchman] <i>Ma'am, we have Datu Rahman.</i>

67
00:03:04,726 --> 00:03:05,602
[man chuckles]

68
00:03:05,685 --> 00:03:06,978
[relieved sigh, in English] Good.

69
00:03:09,731 --> 00:03:10,857
[man] Let's go!

70
00:03:11,608 --> 00:03:12,567
[man] Don't scream!

71
00:03:12,650 --> 00:03:14,027
[tense music playing]

72
00:03:14,652 --> 00:03:17,530
[engine starts]

73
00:03:19,490 --> 00:03:21,784
[tense music continues]

74
00:03:27,081 --> 00:03:30,001
[Jalil] <i>I will not let them</i>
<i>take you again, Father.</i>

75
00:03:31,002 --> 00:03:32,503
<i>You are coming home with me.</i>

76
00:03:32,587 --> 00:03:33,504
[music concludes]

77
00:03:33,588 --> 00:03:34,756
[crickets chirping]

78
00:03:34,839 --> 00:03:37,592
[suspenseful music playing]

79
00:03:51,397 --> 00:03:53,316
[boat engine whirring]

80
00:04:03,326 --> 00:04:05,703
[suspenseful music continues]

81
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:22,804
- [man 1] Unload everything.
- [man 2] Okay.

82
00:04:22,887 --> 00:04:23,930
[man 3] Come on.

83
00:04:24,430 --> 00:04:27,058
[suspenseful music continues]

84
00:04:29,811 --> 00:04:34,899
[suspenseful music playing]

85
00:04:36,776 --> 00:04:38,695
[man 1] Come on! Hustle!

86
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:40,905
- [man 2] Go!
- [man 1] The boss will be here soon!

87
00:04:40,989 --> 00:04:43,950
The weapons I saw
were recovered from the sea.

88
00:04:44,033 --> 00:04:47,829
And we hid them from the syndicate,
so they couldn't use them.

89
00:04:48,329 --> 00:04:51,541
[suspenseful music continues]

90
00:05:11,394 --> 00:05:14,272
[suspenseful music continues]

91
00:05:19,152 --> 00:05:22,155
[suspenseful music continues]

92
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:36,210
Datu Rahman! [panting]

93
00:05:36,294 --> 00:05:40,173
[panting]

94
00:05:40,256 --> 00:05:41,758
[exhales heavily]

95
00:05:42,425 --> 00:05:43,426
[grunts angrily]

96
00:05:44,594 --> 00:05:46,721
- [man 1 grunts]
- [man 2] Close the door.

97
00:05:46,804 --> 00:05:49,432
[suspenseful music continues]

98
00:05:55,813 --> 00:05:57,523
Are you sure you unloaded everything?

99
00:05:57,607 --> 00:05:58,608
[man] Yes, Boss.

100
00:05:58,691 --> 00:06:00,485
[man] Now that Datu Rahman is gone,

101
00:06:00,568 --> 00:06:02,987
nothing stands in the way
of the weapon shipment.

102
00:06:03,863 --> 00:06:05,198
We're back in business.

103
00:06:05,281 --> 00:06:07,283
But what about the checkpoint, Boss?

104
00:06:07,366 --> 00:06:08,576
We might get caught there.

105
00:06:08,659 --> 00:06:09,619
[scoffs]

106
00:06:09,702 --> 00:06:12,288
They won't stop us. The cops are in on it.

107
00:06:12,371 --> 00:06:14,957
[music turns unsettling]

108
00:06:15,041 --> 00:06:16,667
[panting]

109
00:06:16,751 --> 00:06:18,753
[line ringing]

110
00:06:18,836 --> 00:06:20,213
[breathing heavily]

111
00:06:20,296 --> 00:06:21,464
[ringing continues]

112
00:06:21,547 --> 00:06:23,591
Pick up the phone, bro. [inhales]

113
00:06:23,674 --> 00:06:28,262
[phone buzzing]

114
00:06:28,346 --> 00:06:29,722
[tense music playing]

115
00:06:37,188 --> 00:06:39,232
[suspenseful music playing]

116
00:06:47,657 --> 00:06:48,991
[line ringing]

117
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:52,620
- [exhales sharply]
- [loud thud]

118
00:06:52,703 --> 00:06:55,998
[panicked breathing]

119
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:00,336
[Usman] <i>I need to get Datu Rahman back.</i>

120
00:07:00,419 --> 00:07:01,587
[inhales]

121
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:04,590
[ominous music playing]

122
00:07:04,674 --> 00:07:07,927
[crickets chirping]

123
00:07:21,023 --> 00:07:25,403
[ominous music continues]

124
00:07:31,117 --> 00:07:32,118
[horn honks]

125
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:43,713
[ominous music continues]

126
00:07:44,714 --> 00:07:46,799
- [Datu Rahman grunts]
- [man] Get out!

127
00:07:46,883 --> 00:07:52,597
[Datu Rahman grunting]

128
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:54,140
[Datu Rahman grunts] Damn you!

129
00:07:55,892 --> 00:07:58,311
[suspenseful music playing]

130
00:08:04,567 --> 00:08:06,277
- [henchman] Hurry up!
- [Datu Rahman grunts]

131
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:07,695
Get into position!

132
00:08:09,697 --> 00:08:11,782
[muffled grunts]

133
00:08:12,825 --> 00:08:17,747
[suspenseful music continues]

134
00:08:31,219 --> 00:08:34,138
[music intensifies]

135
00:08:42,438 --> 00:08:44,106
- [Datu Rahman grunting]
- [man] Shut up!

136
00:08:44,190 --> 00:08:47,443
[tense music continues]

137
00:09:02,875 --> 00:09:05,753
[tense music continues]

138
00:09:06,712 --> 00:09:09,173
[Datu Rahman whimpers]

139
00:09:09,257 --> 00:09:15,638
[tense music continues]

140
00:09:16,430 --> 00:09:17,974
[Marcus grunts]

141
00:09:18,057 --> 00:09:24,355
[ominous music playing]

142
00:09:34,991 --> 00:09:36,701
Where are you, Datu Rahman?

143
00:09:40,621 --> 00:09:41,706
[Datu Rahman grunts]

144
00:09:42,206 --> 00:09:44,333
[muffled grunts] What are you doing?!

145
00:09:45,042 --> 00:09:46,252
[grunts]

146
00:09:46,335 --> 00:09:47,920
- [gasps]
- [man] Get in!

147
00:09:48,004 --> 00:09:49,088
[ominous music playing]

148
00:09:49,755 --> 00:09:51,048
[tense music playing]

149
00:09:51,132 --> 00:09:53,009
I know nothing!

150
00:09:53,509 --> 00:09:56,262
You won't get anything from me!

151
00:09:56,345 --> 00:09:58,472
Don't you understand that?!

152
00:09:59,056 --> 00:10:00,516
Listen to me, you bastards!

153
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:03,978
[ominous music continues]

154
00:10:05,771 --> 00:10:07,106
- [Datu Rahman cries]
- [lock jingles]

155
00:10:09,859 --> 00:10:11,027
[grunts]

156
00:10:11,110 --> 00:10:17,116
[tense music continues]

157
00:10:30,171 --> 00:10:31,172
What happened?

158
00:10:32,298 --> 00:10:33,466
Check the breakers!

159
00:10:33,549 --> 00:10:37,261
[tense music continues]

160
00:10:56,614 --> 00:10:57,740
I know who you are.

161
00:10:58,449 --> 00:10:59,575
Marcus Reyes, right?

162
00:11:00,242 --> 00:11:01,494
A cop from Manila.

163
00:11:02,495 --> 00:11:03,621
You've come so far.

164
00:11:03,704 --> 00:11:05,581
[tense music playing]

165
00:11:05,665 --> 00:11:06,749
What are you doing here?

166
00:11:07,375 --> 00:11:09,335
Are you going to confiscate our stuff?

167
00:11:09,418 --> 00:11:11,253
Do you think that'll work?

168
00:11:11,754 --> 00:11:14,006
We've got men on the inside.

169
00:11:15,257 --> 00:11:17,593
High-ranking officials from NLEA.

170
00:11:17,676 --> 00:11:21,806
You can confiscate the weapons
all you want,

171
00:11:22,473 --> 00:11:24,183
but it'll always come back to us.

172
00:11:24,266 --> 00:11:27,812
[tense music continues]

173
00:11:27,895 --> 00:11:29,605
[ominous music playing]

174
00:11:31,148 --> 00:11:32,233
[man 1] Hey! Where are you going?

175
00:11:32,316 --> 00:11:33,526
[man 2] Checking the breakers.

176
00:11:33,609 --> 00:11:34,944
Can I borrow a flashlight?

177
00:11:35,027 --> 00:11:36,612
- [man 1] Here, man.
- [man 2] Thanks.

178
00:11:37,113 --> 00:11:40,533
[tense music playing]

179
00:11:40,616 --> 00:11:42,118
[man] Goodness!

180
00:11:42,201 --> 00:11:43,285
Look closer.

181
00:11:43,369 --> 00:11:44,245
Why me?

182
00:11:46,414 --> 00:11:47,540
Open it up.

183
00:11:47,623 --> 00:11:49,834
Wait a minute. Hold the light straight.

184
00:11:49,917 --> 00:11:50,835
There you go.

185
00:11:50,918 --> 00:11:52,628
[ominous music playing]

186
00:11:52,711 --> 00:11:53,838
It's cut off!

187
00:11:54,338 --> 00:11:55,756
Who did this?

188
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:57,675
How would I know?
I was with you the whole time.

189
00:11:58,592 --> 00:12:00,970
[tense music continues]

190
00:12:06,767 --> 00:12:08,853
[man] Hold the light straight!

191
00:12:11,439 --> 00:12:12,273
[man grunts]

192
00:12:21,073 --> 00:12:25,244
[tense music continues]

193
00:12:40,259 --> 00:12:45,139
[tense music continues]

194
00:12:48,893 --> 00:12:53,689
[suspenseful music playing]

195
00:12:59,236 --> 00:13:00,237
Are you sure?

196
00:13:04,408 --> 00:13:05,993
Can you get it back burnt?

197
00:13:06,076 --> 00:13:07,870
[ominous music playing]

198
00:13:10,998 --> 00:13:12,917
[grunts]

199
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:16,170
[grunting]

200
00:13:16,795 --> 00:13:19,089
[man] What's taking them so long?

201
00:13:21,383 --> 00:13:24,845
[grunting]

202
00:13:30,267 --> 00:13:31,894
[grunts]

203
00:13:31,977 --> 00:13:35,022
[tense music continues]

204
00:13:41,237 --> 00:13:45,991
- [groans]
- [grunting]

205
00:13:50,412 --> 00:13:52,540
[tense music playing]

206
00:13:52,623 --> 00:13:54,041
[screams]

207
00:13:56,335 --> 00:13:57,962
[grunts]

208
00:13:58,045 --> 00:14:03,551
[tense music continues]

209
00:14:22,820 --> 00:14:26,907
[tense music continues]

210
00:14:39,003 --> 00:14:44,174
[grunting]

211
00:14:46,343 --> 00:14:48,137
[suspenseful music playing]

212
00:14:48,721 --> 00:14:53,183
[grunts]

213
00:14:53,267 --> 00:14:56,061
[music intensifies]

214
00:14:56,145 --> 00:14:57,605
- [ominous music playing]
- [grunts]

215
00:14:59,189 --> 00:15:03,402
[grunting]

216
00:15:03,485 --> 00:15:06,906
[grunts]

217
00:15:06,989 --> 00:15:09,992
[men grunting]

218
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:20,461
[tense music playing]

219
00:15:20,544 --> 00:15:21,545
[man] Where's my partner?

220
00:15:21,629 --> 00:15:26,467
[music turns suspenseful]

221
00:15:30,179 --> 00:15:32,806
[tense music continues]

222
00:15:36,268 --> 00:15:37,686
[grunts]

223
00:15:39,104 --> 00:15:40,105
[thuds]

224
00:15:49,156 --> 00:15:50,199
[groans]

225
00:15:50,699 --> 00:15:54,119
[groans]

226
00:15:56,246 --> 00:15:58,290
[groans]

227
00:15:58,374 --> 00:16:01,752
[tense music continues]

228
00:16:05,798 --> 00:16:09,677
[grunts]

229
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:11,178
Hey. Hey, man.

230
00:16:11,804 --> 00:16:12,846
[groans]

231
00:16:13,931 --> 00:16:16,308
- [grunts]
- [grunts] Get up.

232
00:16:16,809 --> 00:16:19,478
[grunts]

233
00:16:20,062 --> 00:16:21,313
Ow…

234
00:16:21,939 --> 00:16:23,190
[grunts]

235
00:16:24,024 --> 00:16:25,150
[man grunts]

236
00:16:27,403 --> 00:16:28,487
[men speak indistinctly]

237
00:16:28,570 --> 00:16:30,864
- [man 1] Search over there! Go!
- [man 2] Let's go.

238
00:16:30,948 --> 00:16:32,199
[grunts]

239
00:16:35,995 --> 00:16:38,080
[grunts, groans]

240
00:16:39,123 --> 00:16:40,332
[grunts]

241
00:16:40,416 --> 00:16:44,461
[sinister music plays]

242
00:16:49,299 --> 00:16:50,676
[exhales]

243
00:16:50,759 --> 00:16:53,429
[tense music continues]

244
00:16:53,512 --> 00:16:57,850
[tense music playing]

245
00:17:07,985 --> 00:17:08,861
[sighs]

246
00:17:09,862 --> 00:17:10,904
Papa!

247
00:17:13,073 --> 00:17:18,495
[tense music continues]

248
00:17:36,597 --> 00:17:37,598
Papa!

249
00:17:40,934 --> 00:17:41,852
Papa!

250
00:17:43,270 --> 00:17:44,229
Papa!

251
00:17:51,987 --> 00:17:56,075
[tense music continues]

252
00:18:01,038 --> 00:18:02,915
[suspenseful music playing]

253
00:18:04,875 --> 00:18:06,085
[grunts]

254
00:18:10,839 --> 00:18:11,965
[grunts]

255
00:18:12,549 --> 00:18:15,052
[grunting]

256
00:18:15,135 --> 00:18:19,264
- [grunting]
- [groans]

257
00:18:25,938 --> 00:18:28,524
[grunts]

258
00:18:29,108 --> 00:18:33,320
[men grunting]

259
00:18:33,904 --> 00:18:38,617
[tense music continues]

260
00:18:42,454 --> 00:18:47,126
[grunts]

261
00:18:55,968 --> 00:19:00,514
[tense music playing]

262
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:02,850
Check on them.

263
00:19:02,933 --> 00:19:06,812
[suspenseful music playing]

264
00:19:19,032 --> 00:19:20,325
What happened? Where are they?

265
00:19:20,409 --> 00:19:26,415
[music turns tense]

266
00:19:44,057 --> 00:19:46,351
[tense music continues]

267
00:19:57,237 --> 00:20:02,534
[suspenseful music playing]

268
00:20:03,452 --> 00:20:07,164
[dramatic music playing]

269
00:20:20,135 --> 00:20:21,720
- [boy grunts]
- Peklat!

270
00:20:21,803 --> 00:20:23,388
- I'll kill him!
- No!

271
00:20:26,433 --> 00:20:29,311
[screaming]

272
00:20:29,394 --> 00:20:34,691
[dramatic music continues]

273
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:36,485
Hey!

274
00:20:38,487 --> 00:20:39,363
[man grunts]

275
00:20:59,174 --> 00:21:03,095
[monitor beeping rapidly]

276
00:21:03,178 --> 00:21:06,765
[monitor flatlines]

277
00:21:07,474 --> 00:21:08,475
[man] No!

278
00:21:08,558 --> 00:21:10,852
[Marcus] Oliver! Nurse!

279
00:21:11,478 --> 00:21:12,521
Nurse!

280
00:21:12,604 --> 00:21:17,401
[dramatic music continues]

281
00:21:22,030 --> 00:21:25,617
[man] Even if you confiscate
these weapons a thousand times,

282
00:21:26,201 --> 00:21:28,036
they'll just come back to us.

283
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:33,208
[dramatic music continues]

284
00:21:56,315 --> 00:22:01,653
[dramatic music continues]

285
00:22:16,084 --> 00:22:21,381
[dramatic music continues]

286
00:22:32,559 --> 00:22:33,852
[Lara] <i>He can't get away!</i>

287
00:22:33,935 --> 00:22:35,604
Don't let them take Datu Rahman!

288
00:22:35,687 --> 00:22:36,730
[grunts]

289
00:22:38,732 --> 00:22:41,234
[Marcus] <i>You're the ones destroying</i>
<i>the image of the police.</i>

290
00:22:41,318 --> 00:22:44,446
<i>You'll pay for all your crimes.</i>

291
00:22:45,197 --> 00:22:47,491
[Datu Rahman] <i>Jalil? How did you get here?</i>

292
00:22:47,574 --> 00:22:50,619
You need to leave now! I'll explain later.

293
00:22:50,702 --> 00:22:51,828
[Jalil] <i>Can you still fight?</i>

294
00:22:51,912 --> 00:22:53,163
Just like before, son.

295
00:22:54,039 --> 00:22:55,373
[Jalil] <i>Just like before!</i>

296
00:22:55,457 --> 00:22:57,084
They got Datu Rahman.

297
00:22:57,167 --> 00:22:58,251
I'm on my way back.

298
00:22:58,335 --> 00:22:59,586
[suspenseful music playing]

299
00:23:04,341 --> 00:23:06,927
Find Datu Rahman.
I don't care how you do it.

300
00:23:07,010 --> 00:23:08,470
[Lara] <i>You want to make me happy, right?</i>

301
00:23:08,553 --> 00:23:09,513
I've got this.

302
00:23:10,305 --> 00:23:12,057
- [Jalil] Come on, Father. Let's go!
- [mutters]

303
00:23:12,641 --> 00:23:14,226
Don't do anything reckless.

304
00:23:14,976 --> 00:23:16,144
What do you need with Datu Rahman?

305
00:23:17,229 --> 00:23:19,314
[Jalil] <i>We don't need to kill each other!</i>

306
00:23:19,397 --> 00:23:20,565
Who are you?

307
00:23:20,649 --> 00:23:23,485
[music concludes]
